
sample_irq: Demonstrate how to wait for SOC interrupts

Container sets IRQ watch on SOC interrupts. And polls for interrupts to
occur. When a user SOC interrupt occurs, container checks triggered IRQs by
calling cri_sid_sync().

To run (load and start) container:
$ mwtest.py -c100 run sample_irq.img

Raise SOC interrupt
$ cmtest irq -m 0x4 cmrt

Example QEMU output for above commands
1571136152.237594: [CLO] main:59: Container (watch_irq) starting...
1571136155.277345: [CLO] watch_irqs:49: Poll timeout
1571136155.750025: sic_get_app: found unused app flowid 0x801
1571136155.750038: sic_packet_from_application: CMRT_SIC_SOC_INTERRUPT 0x4
1571136155.751425: [CLO] watch_irqs:46: Triggered IRQs: 0x4
